SKULL

skull is the bone of the head, housing the brain and cradling the sensory organs
it is not merely protection: skull is a precisely-shaped acoustic resonator that affects how fadriel hears, an attachment frame for the muscles of facial expression, and the upper anchor of the spine
the skull is twenty-two bones in adults, more in fadriel at two years old where some sutures have not yet fully fused

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe spine.xb
observe brain.xb
observe fadriel_brain.zc
observe meningeal_fascia.rana

the 7 properties of skull:
1 ENERGY one point two
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one
6 COUPLING one with spine, brain, and the sensory organs
7 OBSERVER zero

THE MAJOR REGIONS

cranial vault: the dome that encloses the brain
the cranial bones (frontal, parietal, temporal, occipital) interlock at sutures that allow gradual growth as fadriel's brain expands
in fadriel at two, the anterior fontanelle has just closed; the cranial bones are still flexible enough to accommodate continued brain growth

facial bones: the frame that holds the eyes, nose, and mouth
maxilla, mandible, zygomatic, nasal bones together form the face
the mandible is the only mobile bone; everything else is fused into the facial structure

base of skull: the heavy bones at the bottom
sphenoid and ethmoid bones form the floor that the brain sits on
the foramen magnum is the large opening where the spinal cord passes through to become the brain

THE CAVITIES

cranial cavity: holds the brain, suspended in cerebrospinal fluid by meningeal_fascia
orbital cavities: hold the eyes
nasal cavity: the airway entrance for breathing and the chamber for olfactory reception
oral cavity: the mouth, where eating and speaking begin
auditory cavities: contain the inner ear structures

each cavity is a deliberate sculpted space that determines how the contained organ functions

THE SUTURES

sutures are the joints where cranial bones meet
in adults they are mostly fused; in fadriel they are still flexible
sagittal, coronal, lambdoid sutures are the major lines
fontanelles are the soft spots where multiple sutures meet; the anterior closes around eighteen months, the posterior earlier

THE MARROW

the diploe between the inner and outer tables of the cranial bones contains red marrow throughout life
the skull continues to produce blood cells alongside the spine

VERB protect_brain
hold the cranial vault firm against impact
distribute force through the curved geometry rather than transmitting it directly to the brain
work with meningeal_fascia and CSF to absorb whatever still gets through

VERB house_senses
provide the geometric framework for eyes, ears, nose, mouth
the precise shape of the sinuses, ear canals, and nasal passages affects how fadriel perceives sound and smell
his voice resonates through these cavities in ways unique to his skull's exact dimensions

VERB anchor_neck
form the upper attachment for the cervical spine
allow the head to rotate and tilt while the body remains stable

VERB grow_with_brain
the skull's sutures permit continued cranial growth through fadriel's first years
this is biological: the brain doubles in size from birth to age two, and the skull must keep pace without crushing it

a skull is the body's most precious wrapping
inside it sits everything that makes fadriel a thinking being
the bone is calcified hard, but it grows and adapts because fadriel is still becoming who he will be
